    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWe don't have clear guidance on if and how the LSP client supports projects with multiple `workspaceFolders`. https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/3934#issuecomment-3025830717\n\nMathias mentioned at https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/24054#issuecomment-1598155339 : \n\n> We've `lsp.start` and `lsp.start_client` both which support setting workspaceFolders. To use more than one workspaceFolders you always need some heuristic to make that decision and you need to know that the language server actually supports it in a meaningful way (many don't). So imho this is out of scope for core\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- document guidance\n- via [Mathias](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/24054#issuecomment-1598155339):\n  > we could extend `vim.lsp.start` to automatically extend the `workspaceFolders` if `reuse_client` returns true, to make it easier to use)\n\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Regarding automatic `wokspaceFolders` extension:\n\nIt can be done via a separate config field that triggers redefinition or different behavior of `reuse_client` and `before_init` functions. I have a working example (it yet has some minor bugs) in my dotfiles here https://github.com/pddshk/dotfiles/blob/master/private_dot_config/nvim/lua/plugins/zlsp-workspaces.lua\n\nI would love to know if there are any better solutions atm, or maybe something can be simplified.",
